		</div>
		<div class="details">
			by
			<a href="//use.perl.org/~Yanick/">Yanick (3196)</a>
			
			
			<span class="otherdetails" id="comment_otherdetails_63964"></span>
		</div>
	</div>
	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_63964"><p>It is covered.  And provided that your class is relatively
plain vanilla, the <i>dump()</i> method will do what you want:
</p><blockquote><div><p> <tt>package Foo;<br>use Object::InsideOut;<br>my @x : Field<nobr> <wbr></nobr>:Acc('x')<nobr> <wbr></nobr>:Default('foo');<br>my @y : Field<nobr> <wbr></nobr>:Acc('y')<nobr> <wbr></nobr>:Default('bar');<br>my @z : Field<nobr> <wbr></nobr>:Acc('z')<nobr> <wbr></nobr>:Default('baz');<br> <br>package main;<br>my $obj = Foo-&gt;new;<br> <br>use Data::Dumper;<br>say Dumper $obj-&gt;dump;</tt> </p></div></blockquote></div>
		
	
	</div>
	<div class="commentSub" id="comment_sub_63964"></div>

